(72, 1, '2014-04-07 08:47:41', '2014-04-07 12:47:41', 'Rick is the “patriarch” of the Orlo family. His first introduction to the beauty industry was in the early 1960s, when he drove his Aunt Carmey to beauty school from Gloversville to Albany everyday. Was it all the pretty women, or was it the energy and excitement of the business that intrigued him the most? From that time on, he was hooked. After gaining experience in the salon as a licensed cosmetologist, he became engrossed in teaching cosmetology. At the time, Sassoon was becoming a household name, and Leo Passage was revolutionizing the way cosmetology was taught with his scientific approach to hairdressing. The industry was going through a transformation, and Rick was at the forefront. He became a platform artist for the Clairol Company and won numerous awards for his hair-cutting and hair-styling skills. He also trained several of his students to compete in local and national styling competitions.\r\n\r\nOver the years, Rick has learned the “ins and outs” of the beauty school business and all that the industry entails. Thousands of successful cosmetologists have graduated from his schools. After marrying Alice in 1984, they went into the beauty school business together, first with Colonna Beauty School where Rick had worked since the early 1960s. In 1995, they purchased The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology to provide a more convenient location for their students. Rick is now grooming his children, Angela and Andrew to hone their skills to carry on the tradition to the next generation. “Hairdressing and cosmetology have always been my passion. I take great pride in our many accomplished students who have gone on to have their own successful careers in the industry.”', 'Rick Caputo', 'President - CEO/Owner', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'faculty-name', '', '', '2014-10-02 11:06:36', '2014-10-02 15:06:36', '', 0, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//?post_type=employee&#038;p=72', 0, 'employee', '', 0),
(208, 2, '2014-04-14 17:10:38', '2014-04-14 21:10:38', 'The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology is committed to instructing students in the skills and principles of Cosmetology and Nail Technology. Our curriculum is designed to prepare students to successfully pass the New York Department of State and Appearance Enhancement and Nail Technology examinations, earn their cosmetology licenses and help them begin long-term careers within our industry. \n\nWhy Cosmetology? \n\nAt Orlo, we are passionate about cosmetology, and our students are, too. Working in the cosmetology industry allows us to make personal connections with people, surround ourselves with creative minds, and learn and experiment with new techniques throughout our careers. The services learned in beauty school are always in demand, ensuring the skills you develop today will be valued for years to come. \n\nIn addition to learning the arts and sciences of hair, skin and nails, career opportunities available to the licensed cosmetologist include:\n\nHairdresser\nNail Technician\nEsthetician\nBeauticians\n•	Salon Manager\n•	Platform Artist\n•	Sales Representative\n•	Consulting\n•	Make-up Artist\n\n\n… and many more!\n\n<h2>The Cosmetology Program</h3>\n\nTo graduate, students must satisfactorily complete the 1000-hour Cosmetology curriculum in accordance with our Satisfactory Progress Policy and satisfy all monetary obligations to the school. Graduates then receive a diploma, which states that they have successfully completed the required 1000 hours of training and are eligible for a temporary cosmetology license. They are then qualified to take the New York State Licensing Exam. \n', 'Program', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '6-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-04-14 17:10:38', '2014-04-14 21:10:38', '', 6, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/6-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(73, 1, '2014-04-07 08:47:22', '2014-04-07 12:47:22', '', '236', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '236', '', '', '2014-04-07 08:47:22', '2014-04-07 12:47:22', '', 72, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//wp-content/uploads/2014/04/236.jpeg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(74, 1, '2014-04-08 08:48:25', '2014-04-08 12:48:25', 'What drew Alice to the cosmetology industry? “It was the creative aspect of it and being able to work with my hands in a friendly atmosphere where they played good music all of the time. The salon atmosphere is the best.” With experience in the industry since 1978, Alice worked in salons and as a beauty school instructor before becoming a director of former sister school Colonna in 1989 then an owner/director of Orlo in 1995.\r\n\r\nShe loves seeing new people find a profession in which they can feel comfortable and can grow. It’s rewarding. Cosmetology is a journey and it’s always changing. You’re always learning new things and meeting new people, and she loves every minute of it.', 'Alice Caputo', 'Director/Owner', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'john-doe', '', '', '2014-06-27 12:18:14', '2014-06-27 16:18:14', '', 0, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//?post_type=employee&#038;p=74', 0, 'employee', '', 0),
(207, 2, '2014-04-14 17:08:42', '2014-04-14 21:08:42', 'The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology is conveniently located at 232 North Allen Street, just a block from Central Avenue in Albany, New York. Easily accessible by local bus lines and interstates such as I-90 and I-87, there is ample street parking upon arrival. Shopping centers, restaurants and other <a href="http://www.theorloschool.com//community/city-highlights/" title="City Highlights" target="_blank">city highlights</a> are close by, making our cosmetology school and the Capital Region enjoyable places to spend your days. \r\n\r\n[button url="https://www.google.com/maps/place/The+Orlo+School+of+Hair+Design+And+Cosmetology/@42.673882,-73.784487,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m2!3m1!1s0x89de0bae131e0663:0x5d238d52fbb58472"]Get Directions[/button]\r\n\r\n[button url="http://overit.com" color="purple"]Color Test[/button]', 'Location', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '50-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-14 17:08:42', '2014-04-14 21:08:42', '', 50, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/50-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(75, 1, '2014-04-09 08:48:44', '2014-04-09 12:48:44', 'Angela literally grew up in the beauty industry as the owners'' daughter. After receiving her BA from SUNY New Paltz in sociology and art, she decided to return to Albany to work in the family business. She loves the flexibility and variety that you get daily working in the cosmetology industry, and she also enjoys getting the opportunity to incorporate her love of photography by doing photo shoots with the students. Angela is a director at The Orlo School, and she also manages Studio Orlo, our Aveda salon in Niskayuna, NY. “The beauty industry is such a fun and rewarding industry to be a part of. We get to spend all day in an uplifting environment making other people feel good about themselves!”', 'Angela Caputo', 'Creative Director/Owner', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'angela-caputo', '', '', '2014-10-02 11:02:37', '2014-10-02 15:02:37', '', 0, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//?post_type=employee&#038;p=75', 0, 'employee', '', 0),
(205, 2, '2014-04-10 17:07:22', '2014-04-10 21:07:22', 'Andrew was born into the beauty industry. Having grown up in Albany at The Orlo school of Hair Design &amp; Cosmetology, being a hairstylist was low on his list of passions and career ambitions. It wasn''t until he started working full time at the school that he realized the impact of the beauty industry. "<em>Beauty changes lives</em>, and it has certainly changed mine. Ever since I started working at Orlo, I''ve become a whole new person. I was one of the shyest kids growing up. Being in this industry quickly changed that, as it truly brings you out of your shell. Hairstylists touch peoples'' lives, we give people a sense of self confidence through the power of appearance enhancement. When you look good, you feel good. Everyone excels when they feel good!" Andrew eventually enrolled in Orlo''s cosmetology course and became a licensed cosmetologist in September 2011. "I look forward to being the future of my parents'' long history and keeping up the tradition of the family business here at Orlo."', 'Andrew Caputo', 'Director of Operations/Owner', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'andrew-caputo', '', '', '2014-10-02 10:43:48', '2014-10-02 14:43:48', '', 0, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//?post_type=employee&#038;p=205', 0, 'employee', '', 0),
(206, 2, '2014-04-14 17:08:29', '2014-04-14 21:08:29', 'The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology is conveniently located at 232 North Allen Street, just a block from Central Avenue in Albany, New York. Easily accessible by local bus lines and interstates such as I-90 and I-87, there is ample street parking upon arrival. Shopping centers, restaurants and other <a href="http://www.theorloschool.com//community/city-highlights/" title="City Highlights" target="_blank">city highlights</a> are close by, making our cosmetology school and the Capital Region enjoyable places to spend your days. \r\n\r\n[button url="https://www.google.com/maps/place/The+Orlo+School+of+Hair+Design+And+Cosmetology/@42.673882,-73.784487,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m2!3m1!1s0x89de0bae131e0663:0x5d238d52fbb58472"]Get Directions[/button]\r\n\r\n[button url="http://overit.com" color="purple"]Color Test[/button]', 'Location', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '50-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-04-14 17:08:29', '2014-04-14 21:08:29', '', 50, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/50-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
