(212, 2, '2014-04-14 17:13:49', '2014-04-14 21:13:49', 'The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology is committed to instructing students in the skills and principles of Cosmetology and Nail Technology. Our curriculum is designed to prepare students to successfully pass the New York Department of State and Appearance Enhancement and Nail Technology examinations, earn their cosmetology licenses and help them begin long-term careers within our industry.\r\n\r\n<h3>Why Cosmetology?</h3>\r\n\r\nAt Orlo, we are passionate about cosmetology, and our students are, too. Working in the cosmetology industry allows us to make personal connections with people, surround ourselves with creative minds, and learn and experiment with new techniques throughout our careers. The services learned in beauty school are always in demand, ensuring the skills you develop today will be valued for years to come.\r\n\r\nIn addition to learning the arts and sciences of hair, skin and nails, career opportunities available to the licensed cosmetologist include:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Hairdresser</li>\r\n	<li>Nail Technician</li>\r\n	<li>Esthetician</li>\r\n	<li>Beauticians</li>\r\n	<li>Salon Manager</li>\r\n	<li>Platform Artist</li>\r\n	<li>Sales Representative</li>\r\n	<li>Consulting</li>\r\n	<li>Make-up Artist</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n… and many more!\r\n<h3>The Cosmetology Program</h3>\r\nTo graduate, students must satisfactorily complete the 1000-hour Cosmetology <a href="http://www.theorloschool.com//program/curriculum/" title="Curriculum" target="_blank">curriculum</a> in accordance with our Satisfactory Progress Policy and satisfy all monetary obligations to the school. Graduates then receive a diploma, which states that they have successfully completed the required 1000 hours of training and are eligible for a temporary cosmetology license. They are then qualified to take the New York State Licensing Exam.', 'Program', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '6-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-14 17:13:49', '2014-04-14 21:13:49', '', 6, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/6-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(198, 2, '2014-04-14 16:56:35', '2014-04-14 20:56:35', 'The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology is an independent, privately-owned cosmetology school devoted to educating new cosmetology industry professionals. Our students move on to a variety of careers, from working as hairdressers, makeup artists and estheticians to owning independent beauty salons and representing major industry product companies.\r\n\r\nAt our cosmetology school, we’re interested not only in the creative aspects of cosmetology but the business of our industry, as well. Our students are prepared to start their own careers, and if they choose, to start their own businesses. While they learn how to style the looks of the individuals in front of them, they also learn how to attract new clients and how to retain them.\r\n\r\n<b>There are a lot of beauty schools - why Orlo?</b>\r\n\r\nWe know the decision about which beauty school to attend can be difficult, but we promise you this -\r\n\r\n<i>We’re passionate about what we teach, and you can tell that as soon as you walk in our doors.</i>\r\n\r\nEvery day, we get to see new students pair their passion for beauty and design with skills that will help them succeed. Throughout our history, we’ve educated thousands of students who have received their cosmetology licenses from the New York State Board of Cosmetology and gone on to bright futures, and we look forward to many more years of education as a top beauty school ahead of us.', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '4-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-14 16:56:35', '2014-04-14 20:56:35', '', 4, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/4-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
