age, color correction and more.  \r\n\r\n<h4>Nail Care & Procedures (40 hours)</h4>\r\nFrom manicuring and pedicuring to nail tips, wraps and enhancements, study and practice everything you need to know to work as a nail technician. \r\n\r\n<h4>Skin Care & Procedures (60 hours)</h4>\r\nPeople aren’t just concerned about their hair - they’re worried about their skin and make-up, too. Study and practice skin care, facial services, make-up application and hair removal.  \r\n', 'Curriculum', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '124-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-14 17:17:56', '2014-04-14 21:17:56', '', 124, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/124-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(218, 2, '2014-04-15 12:55:22', '2014-04-15 16:55:22', 'Whether you’re graduating high school now or trying to attend cosmetology school despite your current job keeping you busy, we know a weekday education schedule isn’t for everyone. At The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology, you can find the cosmetology classes you need held during weekdays, nights and weekends.\r\n\r\nOur full-time day, full-time evening and part-time evening programs provide students the flexibility they need to complete their studies on-time and on-budget.\r\n\r\n<strong>Full-time Day: </strong>\r\nMonday through Friday, 8:45 a.m. to 3:15 p.m.\r\n30 hours per week, approximately 34 to 36 weeks\r\n\r\n<strong>Full-time Evening:\r\n</strong>Monday through Thursday, 5:00 p.m. to 10:00 p.m.\r\nSaturday: 9:00 a.m. to 2:30 p.m.\r\n25 hours per week, approximately 40 to 43 weeks\r\n\r\n<strong>Part-time Evening:\r\n</strong>Monday through Thursday, 5:00 p.m. to 10:00 p.m.\r\n20 hours per week, approximately 50 to 54 weeks\r\n\r\n<a title="Tuition &amp; Financial Aid" href="http://www.theorloschool.com//admissions/tuition-financial-aid/" target="_blank">Tuition</a> is the same regardless of the program schedule you choose - we want you to choose the schedule that will provide you the opportunity to succeed!\r\n\r\n[accordion title="School Holidays"]\r\nNo classes are scheduled at Orlo on the following days each year:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>New Year’s Day</li>\r\n	<li>Martin Luther King Day</li>\r\n	<li>Presidents’ Day</li>\r\n	<li>Memorial Day</li>\r\n	<li>Fourth of July (entire week)</li>\r\n	<li>Labor Day</li>\r\n	<li>Columbus Day</li>\r\n	<li>Veterans Day</li>\r\n	<li>Thanksgiving (two days)</li>\r\n	<li>Christmas (one week)</li>\r\n[/accordion][accordion title="Unexpected Closures"]\r\nIn cases of circumstances such as weather and natural disasters, school closure announcements will be available on our website. Additional notifications will be made by personal phone call, radio/TV announcements or on <a href="http://https://www.facebook.com/theorloschool" target="_blank">Facebook</a> as applicable.\r\n[/accordion]\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'Course Schedule', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '126-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-04-15 12:55:22', '2014-04-15 16:55:22', '', 126, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/126-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
