licable.\r\n', 'Course Schedule', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '126-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-14 17:20:59', '2014-04-14 21:20:59', '', 126, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/126-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(220, 2, '2014-04-14 17:21:41', '2014-04-14 21:21:41', 'Whether you’re graduating high school now or trying to attend cosmetology school despite your current job keeping you busy, we know a weekday education schedule isn’t for everyone. At The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology, you can find the cosmetology classes you need held during weekdays, nights and weekends.\r\n\r\nOur full-time day, full-time evening and part-time evening programs provide students the flexibility they need to complete their studies on-time and on-budget.\r\n\r\n<strong>Full-time Day: </strong>\r\nMonday through Friday, 8:45 a.m. to 3:15 p.m.\r\n30 hours per week, approximately 34 to 36 weeks\r\n\r\n<strong>Full-time Evening:\r\n</strong>Monday through Thursday, 5:00 p.m. to 10:00 p.m.\r\nSaturday: 9:00 a.m. to 2:30 p.m.\r\n25 hours per week, approximately 40 to 43 weeks\r\n\r\n<strong>Part-time Evening:\r\n</strong>Monday through Thursday, 5:00 p.m. to 10:00 p.m.\r\n20 hours per week, approximately 50 to 54 weeks\r\n\r\n<a title="Tuition &amp; Financial Aid" href="http://www.theorloschool.com//admissions/tuition-financial-aid/" target="_blank">Tuition</a> is the same regardless of the program schedule you choose - we want you to choose the schedule that will provide you the opportunity to succeed!\r\n<h3>School Holidays</h3>\r\nNo classes are scheduled at Orlo on the following days each year:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>New Year’s Day</li>\r\n	<li>Martin Luther King Day</li>\r\n	<li>Presidents’ Day</li>\r\n	<li>Memorial Day</li>\r\n	<li>Fourth of July (entire week)</li>\r\n	<li>Labor Day</li>\r\n	<li>Columbus Day</li>\r\n	<li>Veterans Day</li>\r\n	<li>Thanksgiving (two days)</li>\r\n	<li>Christmas (one week)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Unexpected Closures</h3>\r\n\r\nIn cases of circumstances such as weather and natural disasters, school closure announcements will be available on our website. Additional notifications will be made by personal phone call, radio/TV announcements or on <a href="http://https://www.facebook.com/theorloschool" target="_blank">Facebook</a> as applicable.\r\n', 'Course Schedule', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '126-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-14 17:21:41', '2014-04-14 21:21:41', '', 126, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/126-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(221, 2, '2014-04-14 17:22:37', '2014-04-14 21:22:37', 'The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology is an independent, privately-owned cosmetology school devoted to educating new cosmetology industry professionals. Our students move on to a variety of careers, from working as hairdressers, makeup artists and estheticians to owning independent beauty salons and representing major industry product companies.\r\n\r\nAt our cosmetology school, we’re interested not only in the creative aspects of cosmetology but the business of our industry, as well. Our students are prepared to start their own careers, and if they choose, to start their own businesses. While they learn how to style the looks of the individuals in front of them, they also learn how to attract new clients and how to retain them.\r\n\r\n<h3>There are a lot of beauty schools - why Orlo?</h3>\r\n\r\nWe know the decision about which beauty school to attend can be difficult, but we promise you this -\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<blockquote>We’re passionate about what we teach, and you can tell that as soon as you walk in our doors.\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n\r\nEvery day, we get to see new students pair their passion for beauty and design with skills that will help them succeed. Throughout our history, we’ve educated thousands of students who have received their cosmetology licenses from the New York State Board of Cosmetology and gone on to bright futures, and we look forward to many more years of education as a top beauty school ahead of us.', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '4-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-14 17:22:37', '2014-04-14 21:22:37', '', 4, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/4-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(223, 2, '2014-04-14 17:23:01', '2014-04-14 21:23:01', 'The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology is an independent, privately-owned cosmetology school devoted to educating new cosmetology industry professionals. Our students move on to a variety of careers, from working as hairdressers, makeup artists and estheticians to owning independent beauty salons and representing major industry product companies.\r\n\r\nAt our cosmetology school, we’re interested not only in the creative aspects of cosmetology but the business of our industry, as well. Our students are prepared to start their own careers, and if they choose, to start their own businesses. While they learn how to style the looks of the individuals in front of them, they also learn how to attract new clients and how to retain them.\r\n\r\n<h3>There are a lot of beauty schools - why Orlo?</h3>\r\n\r\nWe know the decision about which beauty school to attend can be difficult, but we promise you this -\r\n\r\n<strong>We’re passionate about what we teach, and you can tell that as soon as you walk in our doors.</strong>\r\n\r\nEvery day, we get to see new students pair their passion for beauty and design with skills that will help them succeed. Throughout our history, we’ve educated thousands of students who have received their cosmetology licenses from the New York State Board of Cosmetology and gone on to bright futures, and we look forward to many more years of education as a top beauty school ahead of us.', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '4-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-14 17:23:01', '2014-04-14 21:23:01', '', 4, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/4-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(224, 2, '2014-04-14 17:23:43', '2014-04-14 21:23:43', 'For the Caputo family, The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology feels just like home. It’s where owners Rick and Alice Caputo’s children Angela and Andrew did their homework after school, and it’s where they remain today as co-directors of the beauty school with their parents.\r\n\r\nThe Caputo family’s cosmetology and Capital Region roots go back decades, beginning at former sister cosmetology school the Colonna in the 1960s, where Rick was an instructor. Rick and Alice, a licensed cosmetologist and instructor after studying at the Colonna, purchased the beauty school in 1989 and became co-directors. Six years later, the couple purchased The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology and fused the two schools, moving all classes to Orlo’s North Allen Street location in Albany. \r\n\r\nOver the years, Orlo has helped thousands of students of all ages and experience levels earn their cosmetology licenses. The school has participated in Capital Region events, partnered with local organizations and launched the careers of many alumni who have gone on to own major businesses in upstate NY and nationwide.\r\n\r\nToday, you can find Rick, Alice, Angela and Andrew actively involved in every aspect of the school’s day-to-day management. Visit Orlo in person and you’ll find them giving tours, helping students with guest services, instructing, answering phone calls - you name it! And if they’re not at the school, they’re probably at <a href="http://studioorlo.com" target="_blank">Studio Orlo</a>, their Niskayuna salon.\r\n\r\n', 'History', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '44-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-14 17:23:43', '2014-04-14 21:23:43', '', 44, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/44-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
