(307, 1, '2014-05-05 09:33:20', '2014-05-05 13:33:20', 'For the Caputo family, The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology feels just like home. It’s where owners Rick and Alice Caputo’s children Angela and Andrew did their homework after school, and it’s where they remain today as co-directors of the beauty school with their parents.\r\n\r\nThe Caputo family’s cosmetology and Capital Region roots go back decades, beginning at former sister cosmetology school the Colonna in the 1960s, where Rick was an instructor. Rick and Alice, a licensed cosmetologist and instructor after studying at the Colonna, purchased the beauty school in 1989 and became co-directors. Six years later, the couple purchased The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology and fused the two schools, moving all classes to Orlo’s North Allen Street location in Albany.\r\n\r\nOver the years, Orlo has helped thousands of students of all ages and experience levels earn their cosmetology licenses. The school has participated in Capital Region events, partnered with local organizations and launched the careers of many alumni who have gone on to own major businesses in upstate NY and nationwide.\r\n\r\nToday, you can find Rick, Alice, Angela and Andrew actively involved in every aspect of the school’s day-to-day management. Visit Orlo in person and you’ll find them giving tours, helping students with guest services, instructing, answering phone calls - you name it! And if they’re not at the school, they’re probably at <a href="http://www.studioorlo.com" target="_blank">Studio Orlo</a>, their Niskayuna salon.', 'History', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '44-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-05-05 09:33:20', '2014-05-05 13:33:20', '', 44, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/05/44-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(225, 2, '2014-04-14 17:23:53', '2014-04-14 21:23:53', 'For the Caputo family, The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology feels just like home. It’s where owners Rick and Alice Caputo’s children Angela and Andrew did their homework after school, and it’s where they remain today as co-directors of the beauty school with their parents.\r\n\r\nThe Caputo family’s cosmetology and Capital Region roots go back decades, beginning at former sister cosmetology school the Colonna in the 1960s, where Rick was an instructor. Rick and Alice, a licensed cosmetologist and instructor after studying at the Colonna, purchased the beauty school in 1989 and became co-directors. Six years later, the couple purchased The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology and fused the two schools, moving all classes to Orlo’s North Allen Street location in Albany. \r\n\r\nOver the years, Orlo has helped thousands of students of all ages and experience levels earn their cosmetology licenses. The school has participated in Capital Region events, partnered with local organizations and launched the careers of many alumni who have gone on to own major businesses in upstate NY and nationwide.\r\n\r\nToday, you can find Rick, Alice, Angela and Andrew actively involved in every aspect of the school’s day-to-day management. Visit Orlo in person and you’ll find them giving tours, helping students with guest services, instructing, answering phone calls - you name it! And if they’re not at the school, they’re probably at <a href="http://www.studioorlo.com" target="_blank">Studio Orlo</a>, their Niskayuna salon.\r\n\r\n', 'History', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '44-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-14 17:23:53', '2014-04-14 21:23:53', '', 44, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/44-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(226, 2, '2014-04-14 17:25:17', '2014-04-14 21:25:17', 'Whether you’re graduating high school now or trying to attend cosmetology school despite your current job keeping you busy, we know a weekday education schedule isn’t for everyone. At The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology, you can find the cosmetology classes you need held during weekdays, nights and weekends.\r\n\r\nOur full-time day, full-time evening and part-time evening programs provide students the flexibility they need to complete their studies on-time and on-budget.\r\n\r\n<h4>Full-time Day: </h4>\r\nMonday through Friday, 8:45 a.m. to 3:15 p.m.\r\n30 hours per week, approximately 34 to 36 weeks\r\n\r\n<h4>Full-time Evening:\r\n</h4>Monday through Thursday, 5:00 p.m. to 10:00 p.m.\r\nSaturday: 9:00 a.m. to 2:30 p.m.\r\n25 hours per week, approximately 40 to 43 weeks\r\n\r\n<strong>Part-time Evening:\r\n</strong>Monday through Thursday, 5:00 p.m. to 10:00 p.m.\r\n20 hours per week, approximately 50 to 54 weeks\r\n\r\n<a title="Tuition &amp; Financial Aid" href="http://www.theorloschool.com//admissions/tuition-financial-aid/" target="_blank">Tuition</a> is the same regardless of the program schedule you choose - we want you to choose the schedule that will provide you the opportunity to succeed!\r\n<h3>School Holidays</h3>\r\nNo classes are scheduled at Orlo on the following days each year:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>New Year’s Day</li>\r\n	<li>Martin Luther King Day</li>\r\n	<li>Presidents’ Day</li>\r\n	<li>Memorial Day</li>\r\n	<li>Fourth of July (entire week)</li>\r\n	<li>Labor Day</li>\r\n	<li>Columbus Day</li>\r\n	<li>Veterans Day</li>\r\n	<li>Thanksgiving (two days)</li>\r\n	<li>Christmas (one week)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Unexpected Closures</h3>\r\n\r\nIn cases of circumstances such as weather and natural disasters, school closure announcements will be available on our website. Additional notifications will be made by personal phone call, radio/TV announcements or on <a href="http://https://www.facebook.com/theorloschool" target="_blank">Facebook</a> as applicable.\r\n', 'Course Schedule', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '126-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-14 17:25:17', '2014-04-14 21:25:17', '', 126, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/126-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(227, 2, '2014-04-14 17:25:47', '2014-04-14 21:25:47', 'Whether you’re graduating high school now or trying to attend cosmetology school despite your current job keeping you busy, we know a weekday education schedule isn’t for everyone. At The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology, you can find the cosmetology classes you need held during weekdays, nights and weekends.\r\n\r\nOur full-time day, full-time evening and part-time evening programs provide students the flexibility they need to complete their studies on-time and on-budget.\r\n\r\n<h6>Full-time Day: </h6>\r\nMonday through Friday, 8:45 a.m. to 3:15 p.m.\r\n30 hours per week, approximately 34 to 36 weeks\r\n\r\n<h6>Full-time Evening:\r\n</h6>Monday through Thursday, 5:00 p.m. to 10:00 p.m.\r\nSaturday: 9:00 a.m. to 2:30 p.m.\r\n25 hours per week, approximately 40 to 43 weeks\r\n\r\n<strong>Part-time Evening:\r\n</strong>Monday through Thursday, 5:00 p.m. to 10:00 p.m.\r\n20 hours per week, approximately 50 to 54 weeks\r\n\r\n<a title="Tuition &amp; Financial Aid" href="http://www.theorloschool.com//admissions/tuition-financial-aid/" target="_blank">Tuition</a> is the same regardless of the program schedule you choose - we want you to choose the schedule that will provide you the opportunity to succeed!\r\n<h3>School Holidays</h3>\r\nNo classes are scheduled at Orlo on the following days each year:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>New Year’s Day</li>\r\n	<li>Martin Luther King Day</li>\r\n	<li>Presidents’ Day</li>\r\n	<li>Memorial Day</li>\r\n	<li>Fourth of July (entire week)</li>\r\n	<li>Labor Day</li>\r\n	<li>Columbus Day</li>\r\n	<li>Veterans Day</li>\r\n	<li>Thanksgiving (two days)</li>\r\n	<li>Christmas (one week)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Unexpected Closures</h3>\r\n\r\nIn cases of circumstances such as weather and natural disasters, school closure announcements will be available on our website. Additional notifications will be made by personal phone call, radio/TV announcements or on <a href="http://https://www.facebook.com/theorloschool" target="_blank">Facebook</a> as applicable.\r\n', 'Course Schedule', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '126-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-14 17:25:47', '2014-04-14 21:25:47', '', 126, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/126-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(228, 2, '2014-04-14 17:26:08', '2014-04-14 21:26:08', 'Whether you’re graduating high school now or trying to attend cosmetology school despite your current job keeping you busy, we know a weekday education schedule isn’t for everyone. At The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology, you can find the cosmetology classes you need held during weekdays, nights and weekends.\r\n\r\nOur full-time day, full-time evening and part-time evening programs provide students the flexibility they need to complete their studies on-time and on-budget.\r\n\r\n<strong>Full-time Day: </strong>\r\nMonday through Friday, 8:45 a.m. to 3:15 p.m.\r\n30 hours per week, approximately 34 to 36 weeks\r\n\r\n<strong>Full-time Evening:\r\n</strong>Monday through Thursday, 5:00 p.m. to 10:00 p.m.\r\nSaturday: 9:00 a.m. to 2:30 p.m.\r\n25 hours per week, approximately 40 to 43 weeks\r\n\r\n<strong>Part-time Evening:\r\n</strong>Monday through Thursday, 5:00 p.m. to 10:00 p.m.\r\n20 hours per week, approximately 50 to 54 weeks\r\n\r\n<a title="Tuition &amp; Financial Aid" href="http://www.theorloschool.com//admissions/tuition-financial-aid/" target="_blank">Tuition</a> is the same regardless of the program schedule you choose - we want you to choose the schedule that will provide you the opportunity to succeed!\r\n<h3>School Holidays</h3>\r\nNo classes are scheduled at Orlo on the following days each year:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>New Year’s Day</li>\r\n	<li>Martin Luther King Day</li>\r\n	<li>Presidents’ Day</li>\r\n	<li>Memorial Day</li>\r\n	<li>Fourth of July (entire week)</li>\r\n	<li>Labor Day</li>\r\n	<li>Columbus Day</li>\r\n	<li>Veterans Day</li>\r\n	<li>Thanksgiving (two days)</li>\r\n	<li>Christmas (one week)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Unexpected Closures</h3>\r\n\r\nIn cases of circumstances such as weather and natural disasters, school closure announcements will be available on our website. Additional notifications will be made by personal phone call, radio/TV announcements or on <a href="http://https://www.facebook.com/theorloschool" target="_blank">Facebook</a> as applicable.\r\n', 'Course Schedule', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '126-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-14 17:26:08', '2014-04-14 21:26:08', '', 126, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/126-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(229, 2, '2014-04-14 17:27:53', '2014-04-14 21:27:53', 'Below are answers to some of the most common questions we are asked. If you have more questions for our team, feel free to contact us at any time.\n\n<b>When are the deadlines to apply?</b>\n\nWe have rolling admissions at Orlo, so there are no application deadlines. New classes begin every month!\n\n<b>What is the tuition for Orlo’s cosmetology program?</b>\n\nThe complete cost of our program is $12,000, including all fees and supplies.\n\n<b>How old do I need to be to apply at Orlo? Is there an age limit?</b>\n\nYou must be 17 years of age or older to apply. There is no age limit for entering our cosmetology program.\n\n<b>Is financial aid available?</b>\n\nYes it is. Find out opportunities and requirements on our tuition &amp; financial aid page.\n\n<b>What is the job placement rate for Orlo graduates?</b>\n\nThe current job placement rate is 77 percent. You can find more information like this on  <a title="Student Disclosure" href="http://www.theorloschool.com//admissions/student-disclosure/" target="_blank">student disclosure page</a>.\n\n<b>When are guest services available?</b>\n\nOur <a title="Student Salon Services" href="http://www.theorloschool.com//community/student-salon-services/" target="_blank">student salon</a> is open to the public Monday-Friday 10 a.m. to 3 p.m.; Monday, Wednesday and Thursday 6:30 p.m. to 10 p.m.; and Saturday 9 a.m. to 2:30 p.m.', 'FAQ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '173-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-04-14 17:27:53', '2014-04-14 21:27:53', '', 173, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/173-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(231, 2, '2014-04-14 17:28:44', '2014-04-14 21:28:44', 'Below are answers to some of our most frequently asked questions. If you have more questions for our team, feel free to contact us at any time.\r\n\r\n<b>When are the deadlines to apply?</b>\r\n\r\nWe have rolling admissions at Orlo, so there are no application deadlines. New classes begin every month!\r\n\r\n<b>What is the tuition for Orlo’s cosmetology program?</b>\r\n\r\nThe complete cost of our program is $12,000, including all fees and supplies.\r\n\r\n<b>How old do I need to be to apply at Orlo? Is there an age limit?</b>\r\n\r\nYou must be 17 years of age or older to apply. There is no age limit for entering our cosmetology program.\r\n\r\n<b>Is financial aid available?</b>\r\n\r\nYes it is. Find out opportunities and requirements on our <a title="Tuition &amp; Financial Aid" href="http://www.theorloschool.com//admissions/tuition-financial-aid/" target="_blank">tuition &amp; financial aid </a>page.\r\n\r\n<b>What is the job placement rate for Orlo graduates?</b>\r\n\r\nThe current job placement rate is 77 percent. You can find more information like this in our <a title="Student Disclosure" href="http://www.theorloschool.com//admissions/student-disclosure/" target="_blank">student disclosure</a>.\r\n\r\n<b>When are guest services available?</b>\r\n\r\nOur <a title="Student Salon Services" href="http://www.theorloschool.com//community/student-salon-services/" target="_blank">student salon</a> is open to the public Monday-Friday 10 a.m. to 3 p.m.; Monday, Wednesday and Thursday 6:30 p.m. to 10 p.m.; and Saturday 9 a.m. to 2:30 p.m.', 'FAQ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '173-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-14 17:28:44', '2014-04-14 21:28:44', '', 173, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/173-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(233, 2, '2014-04-14 17:31:24', '2014-04-14 21:31:24', 'Interested in visiting The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology? Let us arrange a personal tour for you! We’ll show you around our classrooms and student salon, and sit with you to learn more about you, introduce ourselves and our program, answer any questions you may have about our cosmetology school or the cosmetology industry, and discuss the admissions process.\r\n\r\nTours are available Monday through Saturday - contact us today to schedule yours! We’ll respond shortly to confirm your visit.', 'Contact Admissions', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '31-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-14 17:31:24', '2014-04-14 21:31:24', '', 31, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/31-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(234, 2, '2014-04-14 17:31:54', '2014-04-14 21:31:54', 'Interested in visiting The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology? Let us arrange a personal tour for you! We’ll show you around the classrooms and student salon at our cosmetology school, and sit with you to learn more about you, introduce ourselves and our program, answer any questions you may have about beauty school or the cosmetology industry, and discuss the admissions process.\r\n\r\nTours are available Monday through Saturday - contact us today to schedule yours! We’ll respond shortly to confirm your visit.', 'Contact Admissions', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '31-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-14 17:31:54', '2014-04-14 21:31:54', '', 31, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/31-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(237, 2, '2014-04-14 17:42:35', '2014-04-14 21:42:35', 'At The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology, we are thrilled to see our students graduate and move on to terrific new jobs in the cosmetology industry.\n\nBut that doesn’t mean we’re saying goodbye.\n\nOur alumni are active members of our beauty''community – helping current students find new jobs, visiting as special guest lecturers, even coming back to work as instructors!\n\nWe want our alumni to <a title="Involvement" href="http://www.theorloschool.com//alumni/involvement/" target="_blank">stay involved</a>, to get continued <a title="Career Placement" href="http://www.theorloschool.com//alumni/career-placement/" target="_blank">career placement</a> assistance whenever they need it, and to share their <a title="Featured Alumni" href="http://www.theorloschool.com//alumni/featured-alumni/" target="_blank">success stories</a> with us.', 'Alumni', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '13-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-04-14 17:42:35', '2014-04-14 21:42:35', '', 13, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/13-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(433, 1, '2014-06-25 13:48:08', '2014-06-25 17:48:08', 'At The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology, we are thrilled to see our students graduate and move on to terrific new jobs in the cosmetology industry.\r\n\r\nBut that doesn’t mean we’re saying goodbye.\r\n\r\nOur alumni are active members of our cosmetology school''s community – helping current students find new jobs, visiting as special guest lecturers, even coming back to work as instructors!\r\n\r\nWe want our alumni to <a title="Involvement" href="http://www.theorloschool.com//alumni/involvement/" target="_blank">stay involved</a>, reach out for career assistance, and update us on current events and successes!', 'Alumni', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '13-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-06-25 13:48:08', '2014-06-25 17:48:08', '', 13, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/06/13-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(238, 2, '2014-04-14 17:42:54', '2014-04-14 21:42:54', 'At The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology, we are thrilled to see our students graduate and move on to terrific new jobs in the cosmetology industry.\r\n\r\nBut that doesn’t mean we’re saying goodbye.\r\n\r\nOur alumni are active members of our cosmetology school''s community – helping current students find new jobs, visiting as special guest lecturers, even coming back to work as instructors!\r\n\r\nWe want our alumni to <a title="Involvement" href="http://www.theorloschool.com//alumni/involvement/" target="_blank">stay involved</a>, to get continued <a title="Career Placement" href="http://www.theorloschool.com//alumni/career-placement/" target="_blank">career placement</a> assistance whenever they need it, and to share their <a title="Featured Alumni" href="http://www.theorloschool.com//alumni/featured-alumni/" target="_blank">success stories</a> with us.', 'Alumni', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '13-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-14 17:42:54', '2014-04-14 21:42:54', '', 13, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/13-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(239, 1, '2014-04-15 08:34:25', '2014-04-15 12:34:25', '[first-line]cos • me • tology[/first-line]\r\n\r\n[second-line](käzmətäləjē) noun[/second-line]\r\n\r\n<strong>Cosmetology.</strong> It is an education that can be acquired at any age. It is an industry that''s always in demand. And it drives careers that allows people to be creative and interact with others, whether it''s their first day at cosmetology school or decades of industry experience later.', 'Home Page Extra', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '196-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-15 08:34:25', '2014-04-15 12:34:25', '', 196, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/196-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(240, 1, '2014-04-15 08:52:22', '2014-04-15 12:52:22', '[first-line]cos • me • tology[/first-line]\r\n\r\n[second-line](käzmətäləjē) noun[/second-line]\r\n\r\n<strong>Cosmetology.</strong> It is an education that can be acquired at any age. It is an industry that’s always in demand. And it drives careers that allow people to be creative, interact with others and learn forever, whether it’s their first day learning hairstyles at cosmetology school or decades of experience as a cosmetologist later.', 'Home Page Extra', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '196-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-15 08:52:22', '2014-04-15 12:52:22', '', 196, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/196-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(242, 1, '2014-04-15 08:58:56', '2014-04-15 12:58:56', 'We thank you for your interest in The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology. We invite you to contact us at any time to discuss our cosmetology program, guest services, community involvement, job opportunities - you have our attention!\r\n\r\nWe look forward to hearing from you and will respond to all inquiries in a timely manner.', 'Contact Us', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'contact-us', '', '', '2014-05-06 11:38:35', '2014-05-06 15:38:35', '', 0, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//?page_id=242', 0, 'page', '', 0),
