(253, 2, '2014-04-15 09:16:27', '2014-04-15 13:16:27', 'We thank you for your interest in The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology. We invite you to contact us at any time to discuss our cosmetology program, guest services, community involvement, job opportunities - you have our attention!\r\n\r\nWe look forward to hearing from you and will respond to all inquiries in a timely manner.', 'Contact Us', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '242-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-15 09:16:27', '2014-04-15 13:16:27', '', 242, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/242-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(245, 1, '2014-04-15 09:00:37', '2014-04-15 13:00:37', 'Interested in visiting The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology? Let us arrange a personal tour for you! We’ll show you around the classrooms and student salon at our cosmetology school, and sit with you to learn more about you, introduce ourselves and our program, answer any questions you may have about beauty school or the cosmetology industry, and discuss the admissions process.\r\n\r\nTours are available Monday through Saturday - contact us today to schedule yours! We’ll respond shortly to confirm your visit.', 'Contact Us', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '242-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-15 09:00:37', '2014-04-15 13:00:37', '', 242, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/242-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(246, 2, '2014-04-15 09:10:41', '2014-04-15 13:10:41', 'The Orlo School of Hair Design &amp; Cosmetology offers tools and guidance inside the classroom and through one-on-one counseling to shape meaningful employment experiences, assisting students in engaging their passions and achieving their goals.\n\nOrlo''s staff members assist students with:\n<ul>\n	<li>State Board days</li>\n	<li>State Board workshops</li>\n	<li>Résumé development</li>\n	<li>Cover letter development</li>\n	<li>Employment portfolio development</li>\n	<li>Job interview preparation</li>\n	<li>Networking</li>\n	<li>Job placement assistance</li>\n</ul>\n\nIn addition, our cosmetology curriculum covers the following sections of Milady Cosmetology''s Business Skills Course within our classrooms:\n	<li>Seeking Employment</li>\n	<li>On the Job</li>\n	<li>The Salon Business</li>\n\n<h4>When should a student begin looking for a job - while they are still studying or after?</h4>\nExplore potential opportunities while attending school. Do not wait until graduation to begin your search. If you do, you may be tempted to take the first offer you receive.\n\nResearch salon websites and social media accounts that interest you. Look for the salon that will be best for you and your goals. When you''ve identified one or more salons that interest you, create and finalize your cover letter, résumé and references. \n\n<h4>How should students approach looking for their first job in the cosmetology industry?</h4>\nExplore the job market and research potential employers.\n\nAsk yourself: \n	<li>What do you really want out of a career in cosmetology?</li>\n	<li>What particular areas within the beauty industry are the most interesting to you?\n\nThen take action. Explore the job market and research potential employers. Get out there - network! Visit salons and talk to their owners, managers, educators and stylists. ', 'Career Placement', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '128-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-04-15 09:10:41', '2014-04-15 13:10:41', '', 128, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/128-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(248, 2, '2014-04-15 09:11:30', '2014-04-15 13:11:30', 'The Orlo School of Hair Design &amp; Cosmetology offers tools and guidance inside the classroom and through one-on-one counseling to shape meaningful employment experiences, assisting students in engaging their passions and achieving their goals.\r\n\r\nOrlo''s staff members assist students with:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>State Board days</li>\r\n	<li>State Board workshops</li>\r\n	<li>Résumé development</li>\r\n	<li>Cover letter development</li>\r\n	<li>Employment portfolio development</li>\r\n	<li>Job interview preparation</li>\r\n	<li>Networking</li>\r\n	<li>Job placement assistance</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\nIn addition, our cosmetology <a href="http://www.theorloschool.com//program/curriculum/" title="Curriculum" target="_blank">curriculum</a> covers the following sections of Milady Cosmetology''s Business Skills Course within our classrooms:\r\n	<li>Seeking Employment</li>\r\n	<li>On the Job</li>\r\n	<li>The Salon Business</li>\r\n\r\n<h4>When should a student begin looking for a job - while they are still studying or after?</h4>\r\nExplore potential opportunities while attending school. Do not wait until graduation to begin your search. If you do, you may be tempted to take the first offer you receive.\r\n\r\nResearch salon websites and social media accounts that interest you. Look for the salon that will be best for you and your goals. When you''ve identified one or more salons that interest you, create and finalize your cover letter, résumé and references. \r\n\r\n<h4>How should students approach looking for their first job in the cosmetology industry?</h4>\r\nExplore the job market and research potential employers.\r\n\r\nAsk yourself: \r\n	<li>What do you really want out of a career in cosmetology?</li>\r\n	<li>What particular areas within the beauty industry are the most interesting to you?</li>\r\n\r\nThen take action. Explore the job market and research potential employers. Get out there - network! Visit salons and talk to their owners, managers, educators and stylists. ', 'Career Placement', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '128-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-15 09:11:30', '2014-04-15 13:11:30', '', 128, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/128-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(446, 1, '2014-06-27 12:22:53', '2014-06-27 16:22:53', 'The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology offers tools and guidance inside the classroom and through one-on-one counseling to shape meaningful employment experiences, assisting students in engaging their passions and achieving their goals. Orlo''s staff members assist students with:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>State Board prep days</li>\r\n	<li>State Board workshops</li>\r\n	<li>Résumé development</li>\r\n	<li>Cover letter development</li>\r\n	<li>Employment portfolio development</li>\r\n	<li>Job interview preparation</li>\r\n	<li>Networking</li>\r\n	<li>Job placement assistance</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIn addition, our cosmetology <a title="Curriculum" href="http://www.theorloschool.com//program/curriculum/" target="_blank">curriculum</a> covers the following sections of Milady Cosmetology''s Business Skills Course within our classrooms:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Seeking Employment</li>\r\n	<li>On the Job</li>\r\n	<li>The Salon Business</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>When should a student begin looking for a job - while they are still studying or after?</h4>\r\nExplore potential opportunities while attending school. Do not wait until graduation to begin your search. If you do, you may be tempted to take the first offer you receive. Research salon websites and social media accounts that interest you. Look for the salon that will be best for you and your goals. When you''ve identified one or more salons that interest you, create and finalize your cover letter, résumé and references.\r\n<h4>How should students approach looking for their first job in the cosmetology industry?</h4>\r\nExplore the job market and research potential employers. Ask yourself:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>What do you really want out of a career in cosmetology?</li>\r\n	<li>What particular areas within the beauty industry are the most interesting to you?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThen take action. Explore the job market and research potential employers. Get out there - network! Visit salons and talk to their owners, managers, educators and stylists.', 'Career Placement', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '128-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-06-27 12:22:53', '2014-06-27 16:22:53', '', 128, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/06/128-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(249, 2, '2014-04-15 09:12:02', '2014-04-15 13:12:02', 'The Orlo School of Hair Design &amp; Cosmetology offers tools and guidance inside the classroom and through one-on-one counseling to shape meaningful employment experiences, assisting students in engaging their passions and achieving their goals.\r\n\r\nOrlo''s staff members assist students with:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>State Board days</li>\r\n	<li>State Board workshops</li>\r\n	<li>Résumé development</li>\r\n	<li>Cover letter development</li>\r\n	<li>Employment portfolio development</li>\r\n	<li>Job interview preparation</li>\r\n	<li>Networking</li>\r\n	<li>Job placement assistance</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIn addition, our cosmetology <a title="Curriculum" href="http://www.theorloschool.com//program/curriculum/" target="_blank">curriculum</a> covers the following sections of Milady Cosmetology''s Business Skills Course within our classrooms:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Seeking Employment</li>\r\n	<li>On the Job</li>\r\n	<li>The Salon Business</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>When should a student begin looking for a job - while they are still studying or after?</h4>\r\nExplore potential opportunities while attending school. Do not wait until graduation to begin your search. If you do, you may be tempted to take the first offer you receive.\r\n\r\nResearch salon websites and social media accounts that interest you. Look for the salon that will be best for you and your goals. When you''ve identified one or more salons that interest you, create and finalize your cover letter, résumé and references.\r\n<h4>How should students approach looking for their first job in the cosmetology industry?</h4>\r\nExplore the job market and research potential employers.\r\n\r\nAsk yourself:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>What do you really want out of a career in cosmetology?</li>\r\n	<li>What particular areas within the beauty industry are the most interesting to you?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThen take action. Explore the job market and research potential employers. Get out there - network! Visit salons and talk to their owners, managers, educators and stylists.', 'Career Placement', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '128-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-15 09:12:02', '2014-04-15 13:12:02', '', 128, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/128-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(403, 1, '2014-06-20 13:38:58', '2014-06-20 17:38:58', 'Applying to colleges can be an exciting time, even if it’s a bit nerve-wracking. At The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology, we know that choosing your cosmetology school is a big decision, and we understand if you’re a bit nervous about it. Our admissions team is prepared to answer any questions you may have about our beauty school, our program or our applications process at any time!\r\n\r\nOrlo accepts students on a rolling basis. <i>New classes begin every month!</i>\r\n<h3>Cosmetology Program Admission Requirements</h3>\r\nEach applicant must submit the following documents:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Proof of age (the applicant must be 17 years of age) documented by a driver''s license, birth certificate, passport or other State or Federal ID</li>\r\n	<li>Copy of a high school diploma or GED</li>\r\n	<li>$100.00 non-refundable registration fee</li>\r\n	<li>Enrollment agreement</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIn addition, all applicants must attend an interview and have a tour of our school prior to admission.\r\n<h3>Transfer Student Admission Requirements</h3>\r\nOrlo does not recruit students already attending a school that offers a similar cosmetology program. It is our policy to discourage students from transferring beauty schools as it can be costly and may cause an interruption to the continuity of the student’s education.\r\n\r\nHowever, we understand when unforeseen circumstances or hardships may make it necessary to transfer. Relocation from another state or geographic area, inability to complete a vocational or high school program, etc., will be taken into consideration on a case-by-case basis.\r\n\r\nA maximum of 500 hours may be accepted from another recognized school. The transfer process cannot begin until we receive, by mail, an official transcript of hours and grades completed at the previous school. Potential transfer students must also provide documentation that meets our entrance requirements. A personal interview and examination to determine the number of hours that may be accepted must be completed before acceptance. Prospective transfer students will be responsible for all equipment and supplies needed to complete the examination, and the examination will cost $100.00.\r\n\r\nAn hourly rate of $10.30 per hour will be charged for the remaining hours needed to complete our program, plus the cost of kit, books, supplies needed and a $100.00 non-refundable registration fee.', 'Admissions', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '8-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-06-20 13:38:58', '2014-06-20 17:38:58', '', 8, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/06/8-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(254, 2, '2014-04-15 09:21:18', '2014-04-15 13:21:18', 'Applying to colleges can be an exciting time, even if it’s a bit nerve-wracking. At The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology, we know that choosing your cosmetology school is a big decision, and we understand if you’re a bit nervous about it. Our admissions team is prepared to answer any questions you may have about our beauty school, our program or our applications process at any time!\r\n\r\nOrlo accepts students on a rolling basis. <i>New classes begin every month!</i>\r\n<h3>Cosmetology Program Admission Requirements</h3>\r\nEach applicant must submit the following documents:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Proof of age (the applicant must be 17 years of age) documented by a driver''s license, birth certificate, passport or other State or Federal ID</li>\r\n	<li>Copy of a high school diploma or GED</li>\r\n	<li>$100.00 non-refundable registration fee</li>\r\n	<li>All entrance documents (CLIENT MUST CONFIRM THIS LINE?)</li>\r\n	<li>Enrollment agreement</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIn addition, all applicants must attend an interview and have a tour of our school prior to admission.\r\n\r\n<h3>Transfer Student Admission Requirements</h3>\r\nOrlo does not recruit students already attending a school that offers a similar cosmetology program. It is our policy to discourage students from transferring beauty schools as it can be costly and may cause an interruption to the continuity of the student’s education. \r\n\r\nHowever, we understand when unforeseen circumstances or hardships may make it necessary to transfer. Relocation from another state or geographic area, inability to complete a vocational or high school program, etc., will be taken into consideration on a case-by-case basis.\r\n\r\nA maximum of 500 hours may be accepted from another recognized school. The transfer process cannot begin until we receive, by mail, an official transcript of hours and grades completed at the previous school. Potential transfer students must also provide documentation that meets our entrance requirements. A personal interview and examination to determine the number of hours that may be accepted must be completed before acceptance. Prospective transfer students will be responsible for all equipment and supplies needed to complete the examination, and the examination will cost $100.00. \r\n\r\nAn hourly rate of $10.30 per hour will be charged for the remaining hours needed to complete our program, plus the cost of kit, books, supplies needed and a $100.00 non-refundable registration fee. \r\n', 'Admissions', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '8-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-15 09:21:18', '2014-04-15 13:21:18', '', 8, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/8-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(255, 2, '2014-04-15 09:25:03', '2014-04-15 13:25:03', 'Do you have questions for our admissions team or are you interested in visiting The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology? You can reach our admissions team through the form below. \n\nIf you''d like to visit our cosmetology school, let us arrange a personal tour for you! We’ll show you around the classrooms and student salon at our cosmetology school, and sit with you to learn more about you, introduce ourselves and our program, answer any questions you may have about beauty school or the cosmetology industry, and discuss the admissions process.\n\nTours are available Monday through Saturday - contact us today to schedule yours! We’ll respond shortly to confirm your visit or answer any questions you may ha.', 'Contact Admissions', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '31-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-04-15 09:25:03', '2014-04-15 13:25:03', '', 31, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/31-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(256, 2, '2014-04-15 09:25:11', '2014-04-15 13:25:11', 'Do you have questions for our admissions team or are you interested in visiting The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology? You can reach our admissions team through the form below. \r\n\r\nIf you''d like to visit our cosmetology school, let us arrange a personal tour for you! We’ll show you around the classrooms and student salon at our cosmetology school, and sit with you to learn more about you, introduce ourselves and our program, answer any questions you may have about beauty school or the cosmetology industry, and discuss the admissions process. Tours are available Monday through Saturday - contact us today to schedule yours! \r\n\r\nWe’ll respond shortly to confirm your visit or answer any questions you may have.', 'Contact Admissions', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '31-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-15 09:25:11', '2014-04-15 13:25:11', '', 31, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/31-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(257, 2, '2014-04-15 12:24:08', '2014-04-15 16:24:08', 'Interested in applying for The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology’s program? \n\nWe’d love to meet you!\n\nFill out the form below with the preliminary information we need to start your application process. Once we review what you''ve submitted, we''ll move forward with in-person interviews, and finally, work with you to complete the full application. \n\nFORM NEEDED - FIELDS FROM CLIENT REQUIRED (AGE? ADDRESS? LEVEL OF EXPERIEN', 'Apply Now', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '15-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-04-15 12:24:08', '2014-04-15 16:24:08', '', 15, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/15-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(258, 2, '2014-04-15 12:19:59', '2014-04-15 16:19:59', 'Do you have questions for our admissions team? Or, do would you like to visit The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology? You can reach our admissions team through the form below. \r\n\r\nIf you''d like to visit our cosmetology school, let us arrange a personal tour for you! We’ll show you around the classrooms and student salon at our cosmetology school, and sit with you to learn more about you, introduce ourselves and our program, answer any questions you may have about beauty school or the cosmetology industry, and discuss the admissions process. Tours are available Monday through Saturday - contact us today to schedule yours! \r\n\r\nWe’ll respond shortly to confirm your visit or answer any questions you may have.', 'Contact Admissions', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '31-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-15 12:19:59', '2014-04-15 16:19:59', '', 31, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/31-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(259, 2, '2014-04-15 12:20:05', '2014-04-15 16:20:05', 'Do you have questions for our admissions team? Or, would you like to visit The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology? You can reach our admissions team through the form below. \r\n\r\nIf you''d like to visit our cosmetology school, let us arrange a personal tour for you! We’ll show you around the classrooms and student salon at our cosmetology school, and sit with you to learn more about you, introduce ourselves and our program, answer any questions you may have about beauty school or the cosmetology industry, and discuss the admissions process. Tours are available Monday through Saturday - contact us today to schedule yours! \r\n\r\nWe’ll respond shortly to confirm your visit or answer any questions you may have.', 'Contact Admissions', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '31-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-15 12:20:05', '2014-04-15 16:20:05', '', 31, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/31-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(260, 2, '2014-04-15 12:20:42', '2014-04-15 16:20:42', 'Do you have questions for our admissions team? Or, would you like to visit The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology? You can reach our admissions team through the form below. \r\n\r\nIf you''d like to visit our cosmetology school, let us arrange a personal tour for you! We’ll show you around the classrooms and student salon at our cosmetology school, and sit with you to learn more about you, introduce ourselves and our program, answer any questions you may have about beauty school or the cosmetology industry, and discuss the admissions process. Tours are available Monday through Saturday - contact us today to schedule yours! \r\n\r\nWe’ll respond shortly to confirm your visit or answer any questions you may have about our program, teachers, students and school.', 'Contact Admissions', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '31-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-15 12:20:42', '2014-04-15 16:20:42', '', 31, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/31-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(261, 2, '2014-04-15 12:24:17', '2014-04-15 16:24:17', 'Interested in applying for The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology’s program? \r\n\r\nWe’d love to meet you!\r\n\r\nFill out the form below with the preliminary information we need to start your application process. Once we review what you''ve submitted, we''ll move forward with in-person interviews, and finally, work with you to complete the full application. \r\n\r\nFORM NEEDED - PRELIMINARY INFO FIELDS FROM CLIENT REQUIRED (AGE? ADDRESS? LEVEL OF EXPERIENCE?) ', 'Apply Now', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '15-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-15 12:24:17', '2014-04-15 16:24:17', '', 15, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/15-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(262, 2, '2014-04-15 12:24:32', '2014-04-15 16:24:32', 'Interested in applying for The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology’s program? \r\n\r\nWe’d love to meet you!\r\n\r\nFill out the form below with the preliminary information we need to start your application process. Once we review what you''ve submitted, we''ll move forward with in-person interviews, and finally, work with you to complete the full application process. \r\n\r\nFORM NEEDED - PRELIMINARY INFO FIELDS FROM CLIENT REQUIRED (AGE? ADDRESS? LEVEL OF EXPERIENCE?) ', 'Apply Now', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '15-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-15 12:24:32', '2014-04-15 16:24:32', '', 15, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/15-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(306, 1, '2014-05-01 14:57:47', '2014-05-01 18:57:47', 'Interested in applying for The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology’s program?\r\n\r\nWe’d love to meet you and discuss how our cosmetology school can help you move toward a successful career!\r\n\r\nFill out the form below with the preliminary information we need to start your application process. Once we review what you''ve submitted, we''ll move forward with in-person interviews, and finally, work with you to complete the full application process.', 'Apply Now', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '15-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-05-01 14:57:47', '2014-05-01 18:57:47', '', 15, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/05/15-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(263, 2, '2014-04-15 12:24:56', '2014-04-15 16:24:56', 'Interested in applying for The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology’s program? \r\n\r\nWe’d love to meet you and discuss how our cosmetology school can help you move toward a successful career!\r\n\r\nFill out the form below with the preliminary information we need to start your application process. Once we review what you''ve submitted, we''ll move forward with in-person interviews, and finally, work with you to complete the full application process. \r\n\r\nFORM NEEDED - PRELIMINARY INFO FIELDS FROM CLIENT REQUIRED (AGE? ADDRESS? LEVEL OF EXPERIENCE?) ', 'Apply Now', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '15-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-15 12:24:56', '2014-04-15 16:24:56', '', 15, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/15-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(264, 2, '2014-04-15 12:27:37', '2014-04-15 16:27:37', 'The following consumer information is provided to assist prospective students and families make a more informed decision in selecting a school. To download as a PDF, click here (LINK).\n<h3>The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology:</h3>\n<strong>OPE ID Number 025876:</strong> This is the identification number used by the U.S. Department of Education''s Office of Postsecondary Education (OPE) to identify schools that are eligible to participate in Federal Student Financial Assistance programs under Title IV regulations.\n\nThis is also the 6-digit number to use when filling out the FAFSA for this school.\n\n<strong>The CIP:</strong> (Classification of Instructional Program) Code is 12.0401- credential level 01.\n\n<strong>The SOC:</strong> (Standard Occupation Classification) Code is 39-5012. The link for the Department of Labor’s O*NET is http://www.onetonline/crosswalk. Use this link for more information about a specific occupation. Use the SOC code above for information about cosmetology programs.\n\n<strong>Costs:</strong> Tuition and fees $10,400, Kit (includes books and tax) $1,600, Total Cost = $12,000.\nThe completion and placement rates listed below were calculated using the accrediting agency’s (NACCAS) methodology as reported in the school’s annual report.\nNACCAS: The National Accrediting Commission of Career Arts and Sciences.\n\n<strong>Completion Rate:</strong> 77%.\n\n<strong>On Time Completion Rate:</strong> 36%. The U.S. Department of Education considers a student who incurs absences (for any reason) that causes them to graduate beyond their contracted graduation date as not completing on time.\n\n<strong>Placement Rate:</strong> 77%.\n\n<strong>The Median Loan Debt:</strong> for Title IV student loans who graduated in the most recent completed award year (2011-12) was $ 5701.00.The median debt for graduates with institutional financing was $878.00 and Private Loan debt was $0.\n\n<strong>Required Books:</strong> (Included in kit price) Milady Beauty and Wellness Bundle ISBN- 9781133025498and Business Fundamental/Salon ISBN–9781428304147 ($535.80).\n\n<strong>Vaccination Policy: </strong><span style="line-height: 1.5em;">The Orlo School does not require vaccinations for admission into our programs.</span>\nNational Center for Education Statistics.\n\nFor more information about enrollment, retention, costs, financial aid, student body diversity by gender and ethnicity etc. click here: www.nces.ed.gov', 'Student Disclosure', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '25-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-04-15 12:27:37', '2014-04-15 16:27:37', '', 25, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/25-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
