(345, 2, '2014-05-21 12:02:58', '2014-05-21 16:02:58', 'On your mark, get set, go!\n\nThe Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology took to the start line for the CDPHP Workforce Team Challenge 3.5 mile road race.  The race is a way for Capital Region companies to promote health and fitness opportunities in the workplace, while providing a sense of camaraderie among employees.  It is the largest road race between Utica and New York City!\n\nOrlo staff and students were up to the challenge this year and coached each other leading up to and during the race.  Everyone ran, jogged and walked at their own pace.  It was not a competition, but rather a team-building event!  Other runners doted on our “Running With Scissors” shirts, while some in excitement shouted, “I just got my hair done there!”.  With the music pumping and the high energy among everyone it was hard not to dance while you ran.  As runners cut corners, Taylor Van Winkler, a current student stated, “We don’t cut corners, we cut hair!”, as she rounded the bend. It was a fun run and The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology knows this will not be their last race!  Be prepared to see us again!\n\nPictured is some of the team before the race.  Can you tell we are all excited?  Check out our fun team shirts!  And of course we had to get a sneaker shot!', 'Running with Scissors! at the CDPHP Workforce Team Challenge', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '101-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-05-21 12:02:58', '2014-05-21 16:02:58', '', 101, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/05/101-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(346, 2, '2014-05-21 12:04:13', '2014-05-21 16:04:13', '', 'Orlo-Corporate-Challenge-2014', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', 'orlo-corporate-challenge-2014', '', '', '2014-05-21 12:04:13', '2014-05-21 16:04:13', '', 101, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Orlo-Corporate-Challenge-2014.png', 0, 'attachment', 'image/png', 0),
(347, 2, '2014-05-21 12:04:20', '2014-05-21 16:04:20', 'On your mark, get set, go!\r\n\r\nThe Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology took to the start line for the CDPHP Workforce Team Challenge 3.5 mile road race.  The race is a way for Capital Region companies to promote health and fitness opportunities in the workplace, while providing a sense of camaraderie among employees.  It is the largest road race between Utica and New York City!\r\n\r\nOrlo staff and students were up to the challenge this year and coached each other leading up to and during the race.  Everyone ran, jogged and walked at their own pace.  It was not a competition, but rather a team-building event!  Other runners doted on our “Running With Scissors” shirts, while some in excitement shouted, “I just got my hair done there!”.  With the music pumping and the high energy among everyone it was hard not to dance while you ran.  As runners cut corners, Taylor Van Winkler, a current student stated, “We don’t cut corners, we cut hair!”, as she rounded the bend. It was a fun run and The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology knows this will not be their last race!  Be prepared to see us again!\r\n\r\nPictured is some of the team before the race.  Can you tell we are all excited?  Check out our fun team shirts!  And of course we had to get a sneaker shot!', 'Running with Scissors! at the CDPHP Workforce Team Challenge', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '101-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-05-21 12:04:20', '2014-05-21 16:04:20', '', 101, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/05/101-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(354, 1, '2014-06-20 13:40:22', '2014-06-20 17:40:22', '<div id="lipsum">\n\nWe love the cosmetology industry, and we love introducing new students to the opportunities it provides us all. If you share our passion, we invite you to explore our employment opportunities.\n\nThe Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology is always looking for qualified applicants for the following positions:\n<ul>\n	<li>Faculty</li>\n	<li>Administrative staff</li>\n	<li>Custodial</li>\n	<li>Reception and support staff</li>\n</ul>\n\nTo introduce yourself and learn about current openings, <a href="mailto:info@theorloschool.com">email</a> us your résumé and cover letter, along with any other materials you think would give us an understanding of your talents and strengths. Reach out to us at any time to introduce yourself!', 'Employment', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '175-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-06-20 13:40:22', '2014-06-20 17:40:22', '', 175, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/06/175-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(404, 1, '2014-06-20 13:40:58', '2014-06-20 17:40:58', '<div id="lipsum">\r\n\r\nWe love the cosmetology industry, and we love introducing new students to the opportunities it provides us all. If you share our passion, we invite you to explore our employment opportunities.\r\n\r\nThe Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology is always looking for qualified applicants for the following positions:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Faculty</li>\r\n	<li>Administrative staff</li>\r\n	<li>Custodial</li>\r\n	<li>Reception and support staff</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\nTo learn more about how you could become of member of our staff, <a href="mailto:info@theorloschool.com">email</a> us your résumé and cover letter, along with any other materials you think would give us an understanding of your talents and strengths. Reach out to us at any time to introduce yourself!', 'Employment', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '175-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-06-20 13:40:58', '2014-06-20 17:40:58', '', 175, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/06/175-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
