(365, 1, '2014-09-23 13:19:49', '2014-09-23 17:19:49', 'For the Caputo family, The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology feels just like home. It’s where owners Rick and Alice Caputo’s children Angela and Andrew did their homework after school, and it’s where they remain today as co-managers of the beauty school with their parents.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nThe Caputo family’s cosmetology and Capital Region roots go back decades, beginning at former sister cosmetology school Colonna in the 1960s, where Rick was an instructor. Rick and Alice, both Colonna alumni and licensed cosmetologists, purchased the beauty school in 1989 and became co-directors and owners. Six years later, the couple purchased The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology and fused the two schools, moving all classes to Orlo’s North Allen Street location in Albany.\n\nOver the years, Orlo has helped thousands of students of all ages and experience levels earn their cosmetology licenses. The school has participated in Capital Region events, partnered with local organizations and launched the careers of many alumni who have gone on to own major businesses in upstate NY and nationwide.\n\nToday, you can find Rick, Alice, Angela and Andrew actively involved in every aspect of the school’s day-to-day management. Visit Orlo in person and you’ll find them giving tours, helping students with guest services, instructing, answering phone calls – you name it! And if they’re not at the school, they’re probably at <a href="http://www.studioorlo.com" target="_blank">Studio Orlo</a>, their Niskayuna salon.', 'History', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '44-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-09-23 13:19:49', '2014-09-23 17:19:49', '', 44, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/06/44-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(366, 1, '2014-06-09 14:13:17', '2014-06-09 18:13:17', 'For the Caputo family, The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology feels just like home. It’s where owners Rick and Alice Caputo’s children Angela and Andrew did their homework after school, and it’s where they remain today as co-managers of the beauty school with their parents.\r\n\r\nThe Caputo family’s cosmetology and Capital Region roots go back decades, beginning at former sister cosmetology school Colonna in the 1960s, where Rick was an instructor. Rick and Alice, both Colonna alumni and licensed cosmetologists, purchased the beauty school in 1989 and became co-directors and owners. Six years later, the couple purchased The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology and fused the two schools, moving all classes to Orlo’s North Allen Street location in Albany.\r\n\r\nOver the years, Orlo has helped thousands of students of all ages and experience levels earn their cosmetology licenses. The school has participated in Capital Region events, partnered with local organizations and launched the careers of many alumni who have gone on to own major businesses in upstate NY and nationwide.\r\n\r\nToday, you can find Rick, Alice, Angela and Andrew actively involved in every aspect of the school’s day-to-day management. Visit Orlo in person and you’ll find them giving tours, helping students with guest services, instructing, answering phone calls – you name it! And if they’re not at the school, they’re probably at <a href="http://www.studioorlo.com" target="_blank">Studio Orlo</a>, their Niskayuna salon.', 'History', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '44-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-06-09 14:13:17', '2014-06-09 18:13:17', '', 44, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/06/44-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(367, 1, '2014-06-09 14:21:07', '2014-06-09 18:21:07', 'At The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology, we don''t want your experience to end when you graduate. Many of our alumni remain actively involved with our school, whether teaching our future students, participating in our events, or working with us on community projects.\n\nIf you are an Orlo graduate, we invite you to reach out to us to find out how you can stay involved with your cosmetology school. There are many opportunities throughout the year.  ', 'Involvement', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '154-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-06-09 14:21:07', '2014-06-09 18:21:07', '', 154, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/06/154-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(368, 1, '2014-06-09 14:21:24', '2014-06-09 18:21:24', 'At The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology, we don''t want your experience to end when you graduate. Many of our alumni remain actively involved with our school, whether teaching our future students, participating in our events, or working with us on community projects.\r\n\r\nIf you are an Orlo graduate, we invite you to reach out to us to find out how you can stay involved with your cosmetology school. There are many opportunities throughout the year - contact us at any time!', 'Involvement', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '154-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-06-09 14:21:24', '2014-06-09 18:21:24', '', 154, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/06/154-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(369, 1, '2014-06-09 14:23:18', '2014-06-09 18:23:18', '<div id="lipsum">\r\n\r\nWe love the cosmetology industry, and we love introducing new students to the opportunities it provides us all. If you share our passion, we invite you to explore our employment opportunities.\r\n\r\nThe Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology is always looking for qualified applicants for the following positions:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Faculty</li>\r\n	<li>Administrative staff</li>\r\n	<li>Custodial</li>\r\n	<li>Reception and support staff</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nBelow you’ll find our current job opportunities at Orlo Design and Cosmetology. Explore the descriptions and <a href="mailto:info@theorloschool.com">email</a> us your résumé and cover letter , along with any other materials you think would give us an understanding of your talents and strengths.\r\n\r\nDon’t see a position listed now that’s right for you but think you can make a difference at our cosmetology school? Reach out to us at any time to introduce yourself, and we’ll keep you in mind for future opportunities.\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Employment', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '175-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-06-09 14:23:18', '2014-06-09 18:23:18', '', 175, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/06/175-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
