\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe students voted on their classmate’s creations.  Check out first, second and third place!  Recognize anyone in first place?  That is Ms. Alice!  Second place is an Under The Sea creation and third place is a Stunning Butterfly.  Awesome job to all of The Orlo students!  You nailed it!\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.theorloschool.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/blog5.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-490 size-full" src="http://www.theorloschool.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/blog5.png" alt="blog5" width="339" height="449" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.theorloschool.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/blog6.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-491 size-full" src="http://www.theorloschool.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/blog6.png" alt="blog6" width="339" height="451" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.theorloschool.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/blog7.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-492 size-full" src="http://www.theorloschool.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/blog7.png" alt="blog7" width="340" height="450" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Orlo Students Nail the Nail Art Competition', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '485-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-07-02 10:14:00', '2014-07-02 14:14:00', '', 485, 'http://www.theorloschool.com/2014/07/485-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(499, 1, '2014-07-02 10:15:53', '2014-07-02 14:15:53', 'Orlo Instructor, Lauren Bastille kicked off the Nail Art Competition with her Nail Art Workshop. Once equipped with this workshop the students had one week to perfect their nail designs and submit one entry for the competition. From bows and flowers to starry nights and swirls there was nothing the students could not paint! Not to brag or anything but The Orlo has a school full of talented students.\r\n\r\nPictured below are the first, second and third place prizes and nail display all set and ready to go!\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.theorloschool.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/blog1.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-486 size-full" src="http://www.theorloschool.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/blog1.png" alt="blog1" width="521" height="521" /></a>\r\n\r\nMs. Bastille you rocked out the Nail Art Workshop!\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.theorloschool.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/blog2.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-487 size-full" src="http://www.theorloschool.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/blog2.png" alt="blog2" width="525" height="525" /></a>\r\n\r\nOur Night Girls having fun with Nail Art too!\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.theorloschool.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/blog3.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-488 size-full" src="http://www.theorloschool.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/blog3.png" alt="blog3" width="525" height="525" /></a>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">The nails displayed and ready for votes!</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.theorloschool.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/blog4.png"><img class="wp-image-489 size-full alignleft" src="http://www.theorloschool.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/blog4.png" alt="blog4" width="401" height="539" /></a></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe students voted on their classmate’s creations.  Check out first, second and third place!  Recognize anyone in first place?  That is Ms. Alice!  Second place is an Under The Sea creation and third place is a Stunning Butterfly.  Awesome job to all of The Orlo students!  You nailed it!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.theorloschool.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/blog5.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-490 size-full" src="http://www.theorloschool.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/blog5.png" alt="blog5" width="339" height="449" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.theorloschool.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/blog6.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-491 size-full" src="http://www.theorloschool.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/blog6.png" alt="blog6" width="339" height="451" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.theorloschool.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/blog7.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-492 size-full" src="http://www.theorloschool.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/blog7.png" alt="blog7" width="340" height="450" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Orlo Students Nail the Nail Art Competition', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '485-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-07-02 10:15:53', '2014-07-02 14:15:53', '', 485, 'http://www.theorloschool.com/2014/07/485-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(513, 1, '2014-09-23 13:53:19', '2014-09-23 17:53:19', '[first-line]cos • me • tology[/first-line]\r\n\r\n[second-line](käzmətäləjē) noun[/second-line]\r\n\r\n<strong>Cosmetology.</strong> It is an education that can be acquired at any age. It is an industry that’s always in demand. It drives careers that allow people to be creative, interact with others and learn forever, whether it’s their first day learning hairstyles at cosmetology school or decades of experience as a cosmetologist later.', 'Home Page Extra', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '196-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-09-23 13:53:19', '2014-09-23 17:53:19', '', 196, 'http://www.theorloschool.com/2014/09/196-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(523, 3, '2014-10-02 09:29:16', '2014-10-02 13:29:16', '<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.theorloschool.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/10715756_10101378110677112_453617260_n.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-519" src="http://www.theorloschool.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/10715756_10101378110677112_453617260_n-225x300.jpg" alt="10715756_10101378110677112_453617260_n" width="225" height="300" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Brittany, a 2013 graduate of The Orlo is a stylist at Hair Studio One in Glenmont.  She has been styling hair at this salon since March and loves it!  As a well-rounded stylist, Brittany specializes in cut and color.  Hair Studio One offers their stylists education in areas of color, cutting, product knowledge and business.  She takes advantage of these classes and loves working with Goldwell color.  Working at Hair Studio One allows Brittany to meet new people and accommodate walk ins all while working in a friendly atmosphere.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">As a fairly new stylist, Brittany offers some advice for recent graduates…. “Do not be afraid to jump right in after you graduate because once you do, it’s very easy!”  Brittany enjoys running promotions on services and products to help build her clientele.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Brittany misses her Orlo Family especially Mrs. Craw, Mrs. Siebels and her buddy Andrew.  She is thankful that The Orlo prepared her for the state board exams and happy for the people she met along the way!</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Bravo Brittany!</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"></p>', 'Alumni Spotlight: Brittany Ambrosano', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '516-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-10-02 09:29:16', '2014-10-02 13:29:16', '', 516, 'http://www.theorloschool.com/2014/10/516-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
