(154, 1, '2014-04-11 09:33:21', '2014-04-11 13:33:21', 'At The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology, we don''t want your experience to end when you graduate. Many of our alumni remain actively involved with our school, whether teaching our future students, participating in our events, or working with us on community projects.\r\n\r\nIf you are an Orlo graduate, we invite you to reach out to us to find out how you can stay involved with your cosmetology school. There are many opportunities throughout the year - contact us at any time!', 'Involvement', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'involvement', '', '', '2014-06-09 14:21:24', '2014-06-09 18:21:24', '', 13, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//?page_id=154', 2, 'page', '', 0),
(279, 2, '2014-04-15 13:12:13', '2014-04-15 17:12:13', '<div id="lipsum">\r\n\r\nCLIENT CONTENT ON HOW ALUMNI CAN REMAIN INVOLVED AT ORLO\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Involvement', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '154-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-15 13:12:13', '2014-04-15 17:12:13', '', 154, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/154-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(317, 1, '2014-05-20 08:35:02', '2014-05-20 12:35:02', 'The Orlo School of Hair Design &amp; Cosmetology offers tools and guidance inside the classroom and through one-on-one counseling to shape meaningful employment experiences, assisting students in engaging their passions and achieving their goals.\r\n\r\nOrlo''s staff members assist students with:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>State Board prep days</li>\r\n	<li>State Board workshops</li>\r\n	<li>Résumé development</li>\r\n	<li>Cover letter development</li>\r\n	<li>Employment portfolio development</li>\r\n	<li>Job interview preparation</li>\r\n	<li>Networking</li>\r\n	<li>Job placement assistance</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIn addition, our cosmetology <a title="Curriculum" href="http://www.theorloschool.com//program/curriculum/" target="_blank">curriculum</a> covers the following sections of Milady Cosmetology''s Business Skills Course within our classrooms:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Seeking Employment</li>\r\n	<li>On the Job</li>\r\n	<li>The Salon Business</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>When should a student begin looking for a job - while they are still studying or after?</h4>\r\nExplore potential opportunities while attending school. Do not wait until graduation to begin your search. If you do, you may be tempted to take the first offer you receive.\r\n\r\nResearch salon websites and social media accounts that interest you. Look for the salon that will be best for you and your goals. When you''ve identified one or more salons that interest you, create and finalize your cover letter, résumé and references.\r\n<h4>How should students approach looking for their first job in the cosmetology industry?</h4>\r\nExplore the job market and research potential employers.\r\n\r\nAsk yourself:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>What do you really want out of a career in cosmetology?</li>\r\n	<li>What particular areas within the beauty industry are the most interesting to you?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThen take action. Explore the job market and research potential employers. Get out there - network! Visit salons and talk to their owners, managers, educators and stylists.', 'Career Placement', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '128-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-05-20 08:35:02', '2014-05-20 12:35:02', '', 128, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/05/128-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(445, 1, '2014-06-27 12:21:12', '2014-06-27 16:21:12', 'The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology offers tools and guidance inside the classroom and through one-on-one counseling to shape meaningful employment experiences, assisting students in engaging their passions and achieving their goals.\r\n\r\nOrlo''s staff members assist students with:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>State Board prep days</li>\r\n	<li>State Board workshops</li>\r\n	<li>Résumé development</li>\r\n	<li>Cover letter development</li>\r\n	<li>Employment portfolio development</li>\r\n	<li>Job interview preparation</li>\r\n	<li>Networking</li>\r\n	<li>Job placement assistance</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIn addition, our cosmetology <a title="Curriculum" href="http://www.theorloschool.com//program/curriculum/" target="_blank">curriculum</a> covers the following sections of Milady Cosmetology''s Business Skills Course within our classrooms:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Seeking Employment</li>\r\n	<li>On the Job</li>\r\n	<li>The Salon Business</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>When should a student begin looking for a job - while they are still studying or after?</h4>\r\nExplore potential opportunities while attending school. Do not wait until graduation to begin your search. If you do, you may be tempted to take the first offer you receive.\r\n\r\nResearch salon websites and social media accounts that interest you. Look for the salon that will be best for you and your goals. When you''ve identified one or more salons that interest you, create and finalize your cover letter, résumé and references.\r\n<h4>How should students approach looking for their first job in the cosmetology industry?</h4>\r\nExplore the job market and research potential employers.\r\n\r\nAsk yourself:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>What do you really want out of a career in cosmetology?</li>\r\n	<li>What particular areas within the beauty industry are the most interesting to you?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThen take action. Explore the job market and research potential employers. Get out there - network! Visit salons and talk to their owners, managers, educators and stylists.', 'Career Placement', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '128-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-06-27 12:21:12', '2014-06-27 16:21:12', '', 128, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/06/128-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(295, 2, '2014-06-06 13:27:44', '2014-06-06 17:27:44', 'From dolls’ hair to friends’ hair to special styles for dances, Amanda has always been interested in cosmetology. She entered the cosmetology field in 2010, and began to work with Orlo shortly after, in 2013. Her favorite part of teaching is helping students grow into the best stylists that they can be and watching them begin to realize their full potential. “If you have a passion for it, you definitely have to follow through on that passion and really give it a shot.”', 'Amanda Kennedy', 'Director/Instructor', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'amanda-kennedy', '', '', '2014-10-02 10:44:58', '2014-10-02 14:44:58', '', 0, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//?post_type=employee&#038;p=295', 0, 'employee', '', 0),
(296, 2, '2014-06-07 13:28:25', '2014-06-07 17:28:25', 'With four decades of experience in the beauty industry, Kath shares years of knowledge, both in styling and in managing her own salon, with her students. She began teaching at Orlo in 2008, shortly after her own daughter finished her schooling here. Kath emphasizes the importance of people skills to her students, which they’ll have the opportunity to develop in the school’s personal and warm atmosphere. When choosing a cosmetology school, she says, “Consider the history and how long they’ve been in their industry. At Orlo, both owners are cosmetologists, and the instructors have different skills, talents and experiences.”', 'Kathleen Siebels', 'Instructor', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'kathleen-siebels', '', '', '2014-06-25 16:07:28', '2014-06-25 20:07:28', '', 0, 'http://www.theorloschool.com//?post_type=employee&#038;p=296', 0, 'employee', '', 0);
